WEBVTT

00:02.961 --> 00:04.874
Hey, how are things going
with your parents?

00:04.875 --> 00:07.676
Not great.
They hired divorce attorneys.

00:07.678 --> 00:09.378
You know, speaking
of attorneys,

00:09.380 --> 00:11.647
if I ever needed
a lawyer,

00:11.649 --> 00:14.950
I would not hire
She-Hulk.

00:15.853 --> 00:17.786
You know what?
That was almost on topic.

00:17.788 --> 00:20.289
I'm gonna say,
"Good job, Sheldon."

00:21.192 --> 00:23.292
Wait, She-Hulk's
a lawyer?

00:23.294 --> 00:25.127
Yeah, she works at
a law firm in New York.

00:25.129 --> 00:28.397
Yes, but she's the only
monster at the firm.

00:28.399 --> 00:30.299
Between you, me
and the wall,

00:30.301 --> 00:33.736
I think she's an
affirmative action hire.

00:34.939 --> 00:36.939
Anyway, Dad's gonna
be here in town,

00:36.941 --> 00:39.475
so I won't be able to do
Christmas dinner this year.

00:39.477 --> 00:41.477
If you're not up
to hosting Christmas dinner,

00:41.479 --> 00:42.711
I'm happy to do it.

00:42.713 --> 00:44.279
You can even
bring your father.

00:44.281 --> 00:46.048
That would be nice.

00:46.050 --> 00:47.182
I've always wanted to do

00:47.184 --> 00:48.817
a traditional
Victorian Christmas.

00:48.819 --> 00:51.820
Parlor games,
goose and figgy pudding...

00:51.822 --> 00:54.490
Ugh!

00:54.492 --> 00:56.024
English pudding.

00:56.026 --> 00:57.793
Y-You get yourself all
excited for pudding,

00:57.795 --> 01:00.829
and here comes a cake
with raisins in it.

01:00.831 --> 01:02.598
I'm not going.

01:02.600 --> 01:03.766
You're going.

01:03.768 --> 01:05.934
Why do you hate me?

01:05.936 --> 01:07.469
I don't hate you.

01:07.471 --> 01:08.437
I love you.

01:08.439 --> 01:09.671
Well, you call it love,

01:09.673 --> 01:11.707
but it has a lot
of raisins in it.

01:14.145 --> 01:15.911
Amy, good luck getting
these guys excited

01:15.913 --> 01:17.312
about a dinner
with a theme.

01:17.314 --> 01:20.949
I gave up when no one cared
about my Tom Hanks-giving.

01:22.153 --> 01:25.154
I think a Victorian Christmas
sounds nice.

01:25.156 --> 01:25.888
I agree.
Why not?

01:25.890 --> 01:26.955
Me, too.

01:26.957 --> 01:29.057
You guys suck!

01:29.059 --> 01:32.661
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

01:32.663 --> 01:35.998
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

01:36.000 --> 01:37.633
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

01:37.635 --> 01:40.169
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

01:40.171 --> 01:42.838
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪<i> We built the pyramids</i> ♪

01:42.840 --> 01:45.507
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

01:45.509 --> 01:47.442
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

01:47.444 --> 01:49.376
♪<i> Bang!</i> ♪

01:49.377 --> 01:53.377
<font color=#00FF00>♪ The Big Bang Theory 8x11 ♪</font>
